15/05/2003
BERLIN, Germany -- The defence ministry announced on Wednesday (14 May) that a German general will assume command of KFOR from Italian Gen Fabio Mini in October.
Lt Gen Holger Kammerhoff will be the second German to command the 25,000-strong force since it was established in 1999.
This number includes about 3,700 German soldiers who are stationed in the area of Prizren.
Kammerhoff will serve as commander for a year.
(AFP, DDP, BBC, B92 - 14/05/03)
